==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ravenala
<hw>Rav`e*na"la</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧v`⟦esl⟧*n⟦aum⟧"l⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Malagasy.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
plants related to the banana.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <spn>Ravenala Madagascariensis</spn>, the principal
species, is an unbranched tree with immense oarlike leaves growing
alternately from two sides of the stem. The sheathing bases of the
leafstalks collect and retain rain water, which flows freely when they
are pierced with a knife, whence the plant is called <altname>traveler's
tree</altname>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ravener</ent>⟦br⟧
